GLESpire for TI-Nspire
=====================

GLESpire is a OpenGL ES 1.1 compatible software renderer designed for the TI-Nspire (but only tested on CX/CX CAS hardware).
It was originally forked from TinyGL by Fabrice Bellard, but with functionality removed to support only OpenGL ES's subset of OpenGL 1.1/1.2. (GLshim/GL4ES/etc will eventually be integrated in some form to resupport the desktop APIs)

The TinyGL context allocates a 16MiB internal arena to use for memory
allocation, but this can be changed by setting `ARENA_SIZE`.

Conformance
-----------
The API mostly adheres to OpenGL ES 1.1 *on the Common-Lite profile* (i.e., only the fixed point APIs), albiet without any extensions. See LIMITATIONS for more detail

Performance
-----------

Do not expect magic, it only runs the gears example at ~30fps in an
emulated CX CAS and half that on real hardware... at half resolution scale.

Build
-----

Install the Ndless toolchain and SDK and make sure `nspire-gcc`, `nspire-ld`, and
`genzehn` are on `PATH`, then run:

```
make
```

The default build creates a static `libTinyGL.a`.

To build the `examples/nspire_gears.c` demo as `nspire_gears.tns`, run:

```
make example
```

Profiler support is compiled out by default. Enable it with:

```
make NSPIRE_PROFILER=1 example
```

Use `make clean` to remove generated Nspire build artifacts.

